SUMMARY:Greater Portland Iris Society Show
DESCRIPTION:\n\n\n\n\n*This show will also be open during Member Hours starting at 9:30am&nbsp\;\n\n\n\nCome celebrate the elegant beauty of irises on June 14\,&nbsp\;2026. The Greater Portland Iris Society will present a show of two varieties of late season irises: iris&nbsp\;ensata (Japanese iris) and spuria.&nbsp\;\n\n\n\nNative to Japan\, Iris&nbsp\;ensata is commonly known as “Japanese iris” outside of Japan. In Japan\,&nbsp\;花菖蒲&nbsp\;(hanashobu) have been cultivated for over 500 years. Oregon and Washington are home to three of the nine specialty nurseries specializing in Japanese irises in the United States.&nbsp\;\n\n\n\nWinners of a previous show\n\n\n\nSpuria\, according to the American Iris Society’s encyclopedia\, “are tall (2 to 5 feet in height) and elegant\, and have very attractive foliage.”&nbsp\;\n\n\n\nAs the Garden transforms into a picturesque&nbsp\;greenscape\, the Japanese iris&nbsp\;provide&nbsp\;a pop of color as the harbinger of summer. The buds open in late June to reveal flowers&nbsp\;nearly six&nbsp\;inches across in shades of purple and white. Symbolizing purity and innocence\, the narrow iris leaf resembles the shape of a samurai sword blade.&nbsp\;\n\n\n
